TAMPA — Want your own Stanley Cup championship bling? Fans attending the Lightning’s home game against the Winnipeg Jets on April 16 will receive replica 2021 championship rings, giveaway sponsor Bally Sports Sun announced Saturday afternoon. Fans will receive their rings and boxes as they enter Amalie Arena. The rings are modeled after the ones the players received in October. Just don’t expect them to have the 338 diamonds and 52 sapphires the authentic ones do. Tickets start at $36.25 and are available at Ticketmaster.com. • • • The Tampa Bay Times has commemorated the Lightning’s second consecutive Stanley Cup title with a new hardcover coffee table book, Striking Twice. Order now. Sign up for Lightning Strikes, a weekly newsletter from Bolts beat writer Eduardo A. Encina that brings you closer to the ice. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.